Additionally, the deployment model of bare metal cloud services plays a vital role in shaping market trends. Public, private, and hybrid cloud options offer varying degrees of control, security, and flexibility, allowing organizations to choose the model that best aligns with their operational objectives and IT strategy. For example, industries with strict data residency requirements or specialized workload demands may opt for a private bare metal cloud deployment to maintain greater control over their infrastructure and data handling practices.

